# 🚗 Vehicle-to-Vehicle (V2V) Emergency Communication System

## Overview

The Vehicle-to-Vehicle (V2V) Emergency Communication System is a web-based application developed to enhance road safety through real-time communication between nearby vehicles. The system enables registered vehicles to exchange emergency alerts such as accidents, vehicle crashes, roadblocks, natural disasters, traffic congestion, and other hazardous situations. The application provides an intuitive user interface for vehicle registration and emergency alert generation while allowing an administrator to monitor vehicle activities and emergency notifications through a centralized dashboard. The project demonstrates the use of modern web technologies and database management to improve transportation safety and emergency response.

---

## Problem Statement

Road accidents and emergency situations often result in delayed communication between affected vehicles and nearby drivers. Existing communication methods rely on mobile networks or manual reporting, which may increase response time during critical situations. There is a need for a reliable platform that allows vehicles to instantly notify surrounding vehicles about emergencies, thereby improving driver awareness and reducing the risk of secondary accidents.

